posts.name: Owen
posts.content: I figured out the random ceasing of function of the site!/n/nWhen the stream page of the site loads, the random post button's random post is predetermined. That means, my computer handles it, not yours. If it selects a post without an ID, it was SUPPOSED to keep retrying until it got a new post that DID have an ID, but a typo made it so that it just keeps checking the same IDless post, over, and over again. This made it so that my computer never responds back to the request. And because the server software is sooooo busy doing absolutely nothing helpful whatsoever, it cannot even listen for other peoples' requests, rendering the site inoperable./n/ntl;dr: Infinite loop in the loading of the random post button if the post didn't have an ID.
